# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.5.0) using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the complete dependency tree

### 2. Analytics Integration
- **Modified:** `frontend/src/App.jsx`
  - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the Router component at the root level
  - Placed the Analytics component after the Routes to ensure it tracks all page views

## Implementation Details

### Framework-Specific Approach
This project uses React with Vite, so I followed the React/Vite-specific instructions from the official docs:
- Used `@vercel/analytics/react` import path (not Next.js or other framework variants)
- Placed the Analytics component at the app root level to track all routes
- The component is rendered inside the Router to ensure proper route tracking

### Code Structure
The Analytics component was added in the main App component which contains the BrowserRouter. This placement ensures:
- All route changes are tracked automatically
- Both public routes (`/`, `/book/:slug`) and admin routes (`/admin/*`) are monitored
- The component initializes once when the app loads

## Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ **Build Test**: Ran `npm run build` - Build completed successfully
2. ✅ **Linter Check**: Ran `npm run lint` on App.jsx - No new errors introduced
3. ✅ **Dependencies**: package-lock.json properly updated with all new dependencies

## Next Steps for Deployment

To enable Web Analytics in production:
1. Deploy this updated code to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in your Vercel project dashboard (Settings → Analytics)
3. Verify tracking is working by checking the Network tab for analytics requests
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard after users visit your site

## Notes

- The implementation follows React + Vite best practices from the official docs
- No breaking changes were made to existing functionality
- The Analytics component is lightweight and won't impact application performance
- Analytics will only send data in production environments by default
